The paper deals with a problem in metric spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves finding a point with minimum average distance, which is related to optimization (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) to prove lower bounds on the query complexity. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS and cs.CG, followed by cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.DM.
